      "writtenOn": "2021-03-04T16:06:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So this is an unfortunate part of using GrAttachment as a class name for now. Long term there won\u0027t be a GrAttachment class at all. It will all be merged with GrSurface. So in that long term world I do think attachmentView makes sense since you really either view a resource as an attachment or a texture.\n\nWe can rename it framebufferAttachmentView(), but that starts getting a little long. framebufferView could also work but can be a little unclear as this isn\u0027t a view of a framebuffer, but a view of something that goes on a framebuffer.\n\nAnyways I\u0027m not really too attached to any names, so happy to take a suggestion if you prefer something.",
      "parentUuid": "63ab925f_ba5dddb9",
